---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import ThemeToggle from '../components/ThemeToggle.astro';
import blogsData from '../../data/blogs.json';
import postsData from '../../data/cache/posts.json';

const blogs = blogsData.blogs;
const totalPosts = postsData.posts.length;

const categorySet = new Set<string>();
blogs.forEach(b => b.categories.forEach((c: string) => categorySet.add(c)));
---

<Base title="About — The Small Web" description="Learn about The Small Web — a curated directory of indie blogs and independent writers.">
  <ThemeToggle />

  <div class="page">
    <Header currentPath="/about" />

    <main class="about-main">
      <div class="editorial-header">
        <h1 class="editorial-title">About</h1>
        <hr class="editorial-rule">
      </div>

      <div class="content">
        <p>This is a collection of indie blogs and publications I've come across over time. The idea is simple:</p>

        <div class="pasted-quote" style="cursor: default;">
          <div class="pasted-quote-inner">
            <div class="pasted-quote-label">The Idea</div>
            <p class="pasted-quote-text">Instead of doomscrolling on Twitter, you could doomscroll here and actually find interesting links — rabbit holes worth going down.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>The only filter I have is whether I've actually read something from each writer. That's it. I'm not curating based on whether I agree or disagree with them — just whether I've found their work interesting enough to keep reading. These are some really smart people, and I think more people should read them.</p>

        <p>I've also included a few aggregators I like — <a href="https://abnormalreturns.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Abnormal Returns</a>, <a href="https://aldaily.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Arts & Letters Daily</a>, and others. They're doing similar work, surfacing good writing from across the web.</p>

        <h2>How it works</h2>

        <p>RSS feeds are fetched automatically twice a day. Posts appear chronologically — no algorithms deciding what you should see. No tracking, no ads.</p>

        <div class="stats-strip">
          <div class="stats-strip-item">
            <span class="stats-strip-value">{blogs.length}</span>
            <span class="stats-strip-label">blogs</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stats-strip-item">
            <span class="stats-strip-value">{totalPosts}</span>
            <span class="stats-strip-label">posts</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stats-strip-item">
            <span class="stats-strip-value">{categorySet.size}</span>
            <span class="stats-strip-label">categories</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stats-strip-item">
            <span class="stats-strip-value">0</span>
            <span class="stats-strip-label">ads</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p><a href="/blogs">See all {blogs.length} blogs →</a></p>

        <h2>About the site</h2>

        <p>I have absolutely no technical knowledge. This entire site was built with <a href="https://claude.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Claude</a> — I just described what I wanted, and we figured it out together. If AI can help someone with zero coding skills build something useful, that feels like a good use of the technology.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="contact-wash">
        <div class="contact-wash-inner">
          <h3 class="contact-wash-title">Know a good blog?</h3>
          <p class="contact-wash-text">If you read someone interesting who isn't here, let me know.</p>
          <a href="mailto:hello@smallweb.blog" class="contact-btn">
            Send a suggestion
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="support-section">
          <p class="contact-wash-text">If you find this useful, you can buy me a coffee.</p>
          <a href="https://buymeacoffee.com/bebhuvan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="coffee-btn">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
